    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Hello world!</p>

<p>Finally my blog is up now.</p>

<p>I wanted to write a technical blog years ago, but because of my lame excuse &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t have time&rdquo;, I couldn&rsquo;t start it until today. Actually I have been playing with <a href="http://wordpress.com/%20Wordpress">Wordpress</a> and <a href="http://www.tumblr.com/">Tumblr</a> before, they&rsquo;re both extremely good blogging platforms. But one year ago I discovered <a href="http://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a> and <a href="http://octopress.org%20Octopress">Octopress</a>, and the idea of blogging using terminal and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown">Markdown</a> sounds awesome to me. The consequence of that is this blog, where you can find my posts about random stuff that I&rsquo;ve stumbled upon, mostly about programming, web development and other tech topics.</p>

<p>To end this boring first entry, here is a random nerdy Chuck Norris joke:</p>

<blockquote><p><span id="joke">Loading joke&#8230;</span></p></blockquote>


<p><em>(refresh to get another one)</em></p>

<script type="text/javascript">
$(function() {
    var url = 'http://api.icndb.com/jokes/random?limitTo=[nerdy]',
        successCB = function(result) {
            var joke = result.type == 'success' ? result.value.joke : 'Something\'s wrong...';
            $('#joke').html(joke);
        };
    $.ajax({
        url: url,
        dataType: "jsonp",
        type: "GET",
        success: function(result) {
            successCB(result);
        }
    });
})
</script>

]]></content>
